            <div style="box-sizing: border-box; display: flex;"><span class="label label-info" style="box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; padding: 0.2em 0.6em 0.3em; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: baseline; border-radius: 0.25em; background-color: rgb(152, 163, 174);">mandatory</span></div>

            <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Prototype: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>char *_memset(char *s, char b, unsigned int n);</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">The <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>_memset()</code> function fills the first <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>n</code> bytes of the memory area pointed to by <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>s</code> with the constant byte <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>b</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Returns a pointer to the memory area <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>s</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">FYI: The standard library provides a similar function: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>memset</code>.             <div style="box-sizing: border-box; display: flex;"><span class="label label-info" style="box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; padding: 0.2em 0.6em 0.3em; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: baseline; border-radius: 0.25em; background-color: rgb(152, 163, 174);">mandatory</span></div>

            <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Prototype: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>char *_memcpy(char *dest, char *src, unsigned int n);</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">The <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>_memcpy()</code> function copies <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>n</code> bytes from memory area <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>src</code> to memory area <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Returns a pointer to <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">FYI: The standard library provides a similar function: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>memcpy</code>.             <div style="box-sizing: border-box; display: flex;"><span class="label label-info" style="box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; padding: 0.2em 0.6em 0.3em; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: baseline; border-radius: 0.25em; background-color: rgb(152, 163, 174);">mandatory</span></div>

            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">Write a function that locates a character in a string.</p>
            <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Prototype: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>char *_strchr(char *s, char c);</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Returns a pointer to the first occurrence of the character <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>c</code> in the string <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>s</code>, or <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>NULL</code> if the character is not found</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">FYI: The standard library provides a similar function: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>strchr</code>.
